   <abstract displayLabel="Description">This is a newspaper article from the front page of the Bogalusa Enterprise and American, 1919 November 27, describing the shooting of Black workers, members of the Colored Timberworkers Local No. 116 union, by a white posse called the Law and Order Division of the Self Preservation and Loyalty League organized along the lines of the Klu Klux Klan.</abstract>
